1312  /**
1313   * The "activities" collection of methods.
1314   * Typical usage is:
1315   *  <code>
1316   *   $youtubeService = new Google_Service_YouTube(...);
1317   *   $activities = $youtubeService->activities;
1318   *  </code>
1319   */
1320  class Google_Service_YouTube_Activities_Resource extends Google_Service_Resource
1321  {
1322  
1323    /**
1324     * Posts a bulletin for a specific channel. (The user submitting the request
1325     * must be authorized to act on the channel's behalf.)
1326     *
1327     * Note: Even though an activity resource can contain information about actions
1328     * like a user rating a video or marking a video as a favorite, you need to use
1329     * other API methods to generate those activity resources. For example, you
1330     * would use the API's videos.rate() method to rate a video and the
1331     * playlistItems.insert() method to mark a video as a favorite.
1332     * (activities.insert)
1333     *
1334     * @param string $part The part parameter serves two purposes in this operation.
1335     * It identifies the properties that the write operation will set as well as the
1336     * properties that the API response will include.
1337     *
1338     * The part names that you can include in the parameter value are snippet and
1339     * contentDetails.
1340     * @param Google_Activity $postBody
1341     * @param array $optParams Optional parameters.
1342     * @return Google_Service_YouTube_Activity
1343     */
1344    public function insert($part, Google_Service_YouTube_Activity $postBody, $optParams = array())
1345    {
1346      $params = array('part' => $part, 'postBody' => $postBody);
1347      $params = array_merge($params, $optParams);
1348      return $this->call('insert', array($params), "Google_Service_YouTube_Activity");
1349    }
1350  
1351    /**
1352     * Returns a list of channel activity events that match the request criteria.
1353     * For example, you can retrieve events associated with a particular channel,
1354     * events associated with the user's subscriptions and Google+ friends, or the
1355     * YouTube home page feed, which is customized for each user.
1356     * (activities.listActivities)
1357     *
1358     * @param string $part The part parameter specifies a comma-separated list of
1359     * one or more activity resource properties that the API response will include.
1360     * The part names that you can include in the parameter value are id, snippet,
1361     * and contentDetails.
1362     *
1363     * If the parameter identifies a property that contains child properties, the
1364     * child properties will be included in the response. For example, in a activity
1365     * resource, the snippet property contains other properties that identify the
1366     * type of activity, a display title for the activity, and so forth. If you set
1367     * part=snippet, the API response will also contain all of those nested
1368     * properties.
1369     * @param array $optParams Optional parameters.
1370     *
1371     * @opt_param string regionCode The regionCode parameter instructs the API to
1372     * return results for the specified country. The parameter value is an ISO
1373     * 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. YouTube uses this value when the authorized
1374     * user's previous activity on YouTube does not provide enough information to
1375     * generate the activity feed.
1376     * @opt_param string publishedBefore The publishedBefore parameter specifies the
1377     * date and time before which an activity must have occurred for that activity
1378     * to be included in the API response. If the parameter value specifies a day,
1379     * but not a time, then any activities that occurred that day will be excluded
1380     * from the result set. The value is specified in ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-
1381     * DDThh:mm:ss.sZ) format.
1382     * @opt_param string channelId The channelId parameter specifies a unique
1383     * YouTube channel ID. The API will then return a list of that channel's
1384     * activities.
1385     * @opt_param bool mine Set this parameter's value to true to retrieve a feed of
1386     * the authenticated user's activities.
1387     * @opt_param string maxResults The maxResults parameter specifies the maximum
1388     * number of items that should be returned in the result set.
1389     * @opt_param string pageToken The pageToken parameter identifies a specific
1390     * page in the result set that should be returned. In an API response, the
1391     * nextPageToken and prevPageToken properties identify other pages that could be
1392     * retrieved.
1393     * @opt_param bool home Set this parameter's value to true to retrieve the
1394     * activity feed that displays on the YouTube home page for the currently
1395     * authenticated user.
1396     * @opt_param string publishedAfter The publishedAfter parameter specifies the
1397     * earliest date and time that an activity could have occurred for that activity
1398     * to be included in the API response. If the parameter value specifies a day,
1399     * but not a time, then any activities that occurred that day will be included
1400     * in the result set. The value is specified in ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-
1401     * DDThh:mm:ss.sZ) format.
1402     * @return Google_Service_YouTube_ActivityListResponse
1403     */
1404    public function listActivities($part, $optParams = array())
1405    {
1406      $params = array('part' => $part);
1407      $params = array_merge($params, $optParams);
1408      return $this->call('list', array($params), "Google_Service_YouTube_ActivityListResponse");
1409    }
1410  }

1412  /**
1413   * The "channelBanners" collection of methods.
1414   * Typical usage is:
1415   *  <code>
1416   *   $youtubeService = new Google_Service_YouTube(...);
1417   *   $channelBanners = $youtubeService->channelBanners;
1418   *  </code>
1419   */
1420  class Google_Service_YouTube_ChannelBanners_Resource extends Google_Service_Resource
1421  {
1422  
1423    /**
1424     * Uploads a channel banner image to YouTube. This method represents the first
1425     * two steps in a three-step process to update the banner image for a channel:
1426     *
1427     * - Call the channelBanners.insert method to upload the binary image data to
1428     * YouTube. The image must have a 16:9 aspect ratio and be at least 2120x1192
1429     * pixels. - Extract the url property's value from the response that the API
1430     * returns for step 1. - Call the channels.update method to update the channel's
1431     * branding settings. Set the brandingSettings.image.bannerExternalUrl
1432     * property's value to the URL obtained in step 2. (channelBanners.insert)
1433     *
1434     * @param Google_ChannelBannerResource $postBody
1435     * @param array $optParams Optional parameters.
1436     *
1437     * @opt_param string onBehalfOfContentOwner Note: This parameter is intended
1438     * exclusively for YouTube content partners.
1439     *
1440     * The onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter indicates that the request's
1441     * authorization credentials identify a YouTube CMS user who is acting on behalf
1442     * of the content owner specified in the parameter value. This parameter is
1443     * intended for YouTube content partners that own and manage many different
1444     * YouTube channels. It allows content owners to authenticate once and get
1445     * access to all their video and channel data, without having to provide
1446     * authentication credentials for each individual channel. The CMS account that
1447     * the user authenticates with must be linked to the specified YouTube content
1448     * owner.
1449     * @return Google_Service_YouTube_ChannelBannerResource
1450     */
1451    public function insert(Google_Service_YouTube_ChannelBannerResource $postBody, $optParams = array())
1452    {
1453      $params = array('postBody' => $postBody);
1454      $params = array_merge($params, $optParams);
1455      return $this->call('insert', array($params), "Google_Service_YouTube_ChannelBannerResource");
1456    }
1457  }

1467  class Google_Service_YouTube_ChannelSections_Resource extends Google_Service_Resource

1470    /**

1474     * for the resource that is being deleted. In a channelSection resource, the id
1475     * property specifies the YouTube channelSection ID.

1477     *
1478     * @opt_param string onBehalfOfContentOwner Note: This parameter is intended
1479     * exclusively for YouTube content partners.
1480     *
1481     * The onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter indicates that the request's
1482     * authorization credentials identify a YouTube CMS user who is acting on behalf
1483     * of the content owner specified in the parameter value. This parameter is
1484     * intended for YouTube content partners that own and manage many different
1485     * YouTube channels. It allows content owners to authenticate once and get
1486     * access to all their video and channel data, without having to provide
1487     * authentication credentials for each individual channel. The CMS account that
1488     * the user authenticates with must be linked to the specified YouTube content

2039     * exclusively for YouTube content partners.

2041     * The onBehalfOfContentOwnerChannel parameter specifies the YouTube channel ID
2042     * of the channel to which a video is being added. This parameter is required
2043     * when a request specifies a value for the onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter,
2044     * and it can only be used in conjunction with that parameter. In addition, the
2045     * request must be authorized using a CMS account that is linked to the content
2046     * owner that the onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter specifies. Finally, the
2047     * channel that the onBehalfOfContentOwnerChannel parameter value specifies must
2048     * be linked to the content owner that the onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter

2052     * many different YouTube channels. It allows content owners to authenticate
2053     * once and perform actions on behalf of the channel specified in the parameter
2054     * value, without having to provide authentication credentials for each separate
2055     * channel.

2057     * exclusively for YouTube content partners.
2058     *
2059     * The onBehalfOfContentOwner parameter indicates that the request's
2060     * authorization credentials identify a YouTube CMS user who is acting on behalf
2061     * of the content owner specified in the parameter value. This parameter is
2062     * intended for YouTube content partners that own and manage many different
2063     * YouTube channels. It allows content owners to authenticate once and get
2064     * access to all their video and channel data, without having to provide
2065     * authentication credentials for each individual channel. The CMS account that
2066     * the user authenticates with must be linked to the specified YouTube content
2067     * owner.
